(79, 185, ' Free Joomla Multilingual Extension', 'free-joomla-multilingual-extension', '<p>The free Joomla Extension for Multilanguage Translation - <strong><a href="http://www.joomlart.com/joomla/extensions/ja-multilingual-component" title="JA Multilingual for Joomla 2.5 and Joomla 3" style="text-decoration:none" target="_blank">JA Multilingual</a></strong> version 1.0.1 for Joomla 2.5 and Joomla 3 has been upgraded to support <strong>EasyBlog</strong> component.</p>\r\n\r\n', '\r\n\r\n<p>If you haven\'t gotten around to know on this brand new FREE Joomla extension for Multilanguage Translation - <strong>JA Multilingual</strong>, here is a quick jot-down on its features:</p>\r\n<ul class="ja-checklist">\r\n            <li>Use BING translation service (sign up for Free)</li>\r\n            <li>Select any language to translate FROM/TO</li>\r\n            <li>Multi languages installation</li>\r\n            <li>Translate all languages in one time</li>\r\n            <li>Easy Association management</li>\r\n            <li>Only translate new content (from the second translation)</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>For more details on this update, please read at its changelog.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Upgrade steps</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul >\r\n<li>View the comparison between versions at <a href="http://update.joomlart.com/" title="Joomlart version update and comparison" target="_blank">JoomlArt Version Updates</a> and replace the affected files, if you have not customized the affected files.</li>\r\n\r\n<li><strong>RECOMMENDED</strong> : Use <a href="/joomla/extensions/ja-extensions-manager">JA extension Manager (JAEM)</a> Component for upgrade. Watch <strong><a target="_blank" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NCufzI-Z6cM&list=PL4BjMzuBkvR_WDwn30cfWF9W9_PUDjiZa">video</a></strong> for how to upgrade using JAEM. Make sure you have latest version of JAEM installed on your site.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Please discuss issues related with these updates in each extension respective f